&lt;em&gt;I thought that the existence of prophecy in Israel concluded with the Anshei K’nesset Ha-g’dola&lt;/em&gt;
Len- There is a detailed introduction on later prophecy and halakhah in R. Margaliot, She&#039;elot u-Teshuvot min ha-Shamayim (1957); Ta Shema, On Shut Min Hashamayim, Tarbitz 57 (1988). Rav Kook discusses shut min hashamayim in his halakhic work. From other perspectives, see Heschel, Heavenly Torah, Moshe Idel has some articles about medieval Jewish prophets and Yuval Cherlow in his Torat E&quot;Y has in the followers of Rav Kook. These articles have the sources. 

